packages

# install.packages("tidyverse")

library(tidyverse)
library(knitr)
library(psych)
library(car)
library(heplots)

# I want recode from dplyr
recode <- dplyr::recode

data

hsb2 <- "data/study1/cleandata/hsb2.csv" %>% read_csv()

custom functions

source("functions/oneway.R")

create contrast variables

hsb2 <- hsb2 %>%
  mutate(lowVhigh = recode(ses_lbl, "Low" = -0.5, "Middle" = 0, "High" = 0.5),
         lomidVhi = recode(ses_lbl, "Low" = -0.25, "Middle" = -0.25, "High" = 0.5),
         acadVgenrl = recode(program_lbl, "Academic" = -0.5, "General" = 0.5, "Vocation" = 0),
         vocVacgen = recode(program_lbl, "Academic" = -0.25, "General" = -0.25, "Vocation" = 0.5),
         ses_program = interaction(ses_lbl, program_lbl, sep = " x ") %>% factor(levels = ))

hsb2 %>% 
  count(ses_program, ses_lbl, program_lbl, lowVhigh, lomidVhi, acadVgenrl, vocVacgen) %>% 
  kable()
ses_program ses_lbl program_lbl lowVhigh lomidVhi acadVgenrl vocVacgen n

model

does social studies score depend on socioeconomic status and program?

fit linear regression

lm1 <- lm(SOCST ~ (lowVhigh + lomidVhi) * (acadVgenrl + vocVacgen), data = hsb2)

results (specific contrasts)

Welch contrasts

see Testing Between-Subjects Contrasts in R

with(hsb2, oneway(dv = SOCST, group = ses_program, contrast = list(lowVhigh = c(1, -1, 0, 1, -1, 0, 1, -1, 0),
                                                                   lomidVhi = c(1, -0.5, -0.5, 1, -0.5, -0.5, 1, -0.5, -0.5),
                                                                   acadVgenrl = c(-1, -1, -1, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0),
                                                                   vocVacgen = c(-0.5, -0.5, -0.5, -0.5, -0.5, -0.5, 1, 1, 1),
                                                                   "lowVhigh:acadVgenrl" = c(1, -1, 0, 1, -1, 0, 1, -1, 0) * c(-1, -1, -1, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0),
                                                                   "lowVhigh:vocVacgen" = c(1, -1, 0, 1, -1, 0, 1, -1, 0) * c(-0.5, -0.5, -0.5, -0.5, -0.5, -0.5, 1, 1, 1),
                                                                   "lomidVhi:acadVgenrl" = c(1, -0.5, -0.5, 1, -0.5, -0.5, 1, -0.5, -0.5) * c(-1, -1, -1, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0),
                                                                   "lomidVhi:vocVacgen" = c(1, -0.5, -0.5, 1, -0.5, -0.5, 1, -0.5, -0.5) * c(-0.5, -0.5, -0.5, -0.5, -0.5, -0.5, 1, 1, 1))))

Does reading aptidude supress, mediate, or confound the relationship between math and science aptitude?

MacKinnon, D. P., Krull, J. L., & Lockwood, C. M. (2000). Equivalence of the mediation, confounding and suppression effect. Prevention science, 1(4), 173-181. .pdf

save math only and math + science models

lm2 <- lm(SCIENCE ~ MATH, data = hsb2)
lm3 <- lm(SCIENCE ~ MATH + READ, data = hsb2)

examine diagnostic plots for the full model

plot(lm3)

simple indirect effect test

mediate(SCIENCE ~ MATH + (READ), data = hsb2, n.iter = 10000, use = "pairwise", plot = TRUE) %>% 
  print(short = FALSE)
